message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with word equations, which are a problem on the intersection of formal languages and algebra.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses a novel technique of recompression applied to the problem of word equations.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the computational complexity of the problem and uses logical reasoning to prove its results.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the word equation problem and provides new results on its space complexity.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of Huffman coding for letters in the word equations.
